last_episode_to_air.name: The Taste of Rebellion
last_episode_to_air.overview: While getting pummeled by Riz, Legoshi realizes that they’re not so different: he could easily have succumbed to his carnivorous instincts, too.

name: BEASTARS
overview: In a world where beasts of all kinds coexist, a gentle wolf awakens to his own predatory urges as his school deals with a murder within its midst.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: Accepting his predatory instincts, Legoshi vows to become stronger for Haru's sake. Meanwhile, the herbivore killer is still on the loose.

episodes.name: The Moon and the Beast
episodes.overview: An herbivore's murder unsettles Cherryton Academy, with some suspecting grey wolf Legoshi. Dwarf rabbit Haru struggles with her classmates' bullying.

episodes.name: The Academy's Top Dogs
episodes.overview: Legoshi ponders his own ferocious impulses; an altercation at breakfast unsettles him further. The theater students prepare for their play.

episodes.name: A Wolf is Born
episodes.overview: Haru and Legoshi's interaction ends extremely awkwardly. With two days to the performance, the school newspaper is sniffing out what Louis is hiding.

episodes.name: Give it Your All
episodes.overview: The drama club switches up parts after the last performance. Tapped to appear onstage, Legoshi confronts the new lead actor about a dangerous issue.

episodes.name: Two Sides to the Story
episodes.overview: Legoshi deals with misplaced notoriety after the chaotic but successful play, with Jack's support. Haru and Louis have a clandestine encounter.

episodes.name: Blurred Vision – Dream or Reality?
episodes.overview: After another murder, herbivores are confined to campus. Out in town, the theater club carnivores enter a shady district for adult meat eaters.

episodes.name: Below the Fur Coat
episodes.overview: The mystery of Legoshi's favorite lunch is solved. Haru recalls her first encounter with a vulnerable Louis, who has a fiancée.

episodes.name: Caught like Floss in a Canine's Teeth
episodes.overview: Legoshi offers to escort Haru home; on the way she attempts to become better friends with him, unaware of his guilt. Juno has a revelation.

episodes.name: Into the Lion's Den
episodes.overview: Louis recalls his harrowing past, and Legoshi makes a personal vow despite conflicting feelings. Meanwhile, Haru is kidnapped for ransom by carnivores.

episodes.name: A Wolf in Sheep's Clothing
episodes.overview: Legoshi risks his life to find the Shishi-Gumi. A friend helps him channel and control his inner beast so that he can save Haru.

episodes.name: To the Neon District
episodes.overview: A ferocious Legoshi wreaks havoc to save Haru, while an unknown ally assists in their escape. Awkward timing causes some awkward situations afterwards.

episodes.name: In the Storm's Wake
episodes.overview: Haru and Legoshi return to school after their strange night. As the festival gets underway, Juno challenges Haru for Legoshi's affections.

episodes.name: A Teen's Never-Ending Alarm
episodes.overview: Things are somewhat calm again, but with Tem's murder unsolved and Louis missing, the school is filled with rumors of hauntings and strange occurrences.

episodes.name: The Grey Police Hound Runs
episodes.overview: Rokume, a giant rattlesnake claiming to be the only security guard in the school, approaches Legoshi and asks him to track down the murderer.

episodes.name: Changes
episodes.overview: After taking a drastic step against the Shishi-Gumi, Louis faces an impossible choice. The drama club gets a new, very confident member.

episodes.name: Entangled
episodes.overview: Legoshi is attacked by a powerful carnivore. As Louis earns the trust of the Shishi-Gumi, he loses his own health and peace of mind.

episodes.name: Call It Like It Is
episodes.overview: While attending school during the day, Legoshi spends his nights in intense training sessions with Gohin.

episodes.name: Fly, O Corrupt One
episodes.overview: Louis wants to officially quit school to make a break with his past, but his father refuses to allow it. Haru and Legoshi talk things out.

episodes.name: Unforgettable Sweetness
episodes.overview: Tao — a black panther — accidentally injures another student. After Legoshi confronts them, the killer thinks back on how and why they murdered Tem.

episodes.name: Laughing at the Shadows We Cast
episodes.overview: After clapping a muzzle on Legoshi, Gohin orders him to capture a beast in the throes of a flesh addiction. Juno ends up spending some time with Haru.

episodes.name: A Busted Electric Fan
episodes.overview: Legoshi is shocked when he meets Louis in the Black Market district. At school, he's disgusted to hear Riz say he'll visit Kibi in the hospital.

episodes.name: The Chef's Suspense
episodes.overview: After Pina makes it clear he won't be intimidated by Riz, Legoshi gets into a bloody bare-knuckled fight with the bear.

episodes.name: Scatter Your Scales
episodes.overview: To grow stronger for his New Year's Day confrontation with Riz, Legoshi tries ingesting a moth larva and has an intense hallucination.

episodes.name: The Taste of Rebellion
episodes.overview: While getting pummeled by Riz, Legoshi realizes that they’re not so different: he could easily have succumbed to his carnivorous instincts, too.

2.name: Season 2
2.overview: Accepting his predatory instincts, Legoshi vows to become stronger for Haru's sake. Meanwhile, the herbivore killer is still on the loose.
